This is not needed if the player is disabled or uninstalled

Go to
HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Microsoft\MediaPlayer\Preferences
and change the DWORD strings
UsageTracking
MetadataRetrieval
SilentAcquisition
to
0

the DWORD string
DisableLicenseRefresh
to
1

the string
SendUserGUID
to
00


&

Go to
HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\WOW6432Node\Microsoft\MediaPlayer\PREFERENCES\HME\S-1-5-21-3279004032-3361476492-3816944365-1001
and change the DWORD strings
UsageTracking
ForceUsageTracking
both to
0


Finish. No restart required.
